# global-site-factory Architecture

`global-site-factory` is a multi-entity company website **generation platform**. Each company website lives as a sibling under `sites/<siteSlug>/` and is built into its own static site. This is NOT a single-site project.

## Directory responsibilities

- `apps/site-builder` — Astro static site generator. Only reads `apps/site-builder/.generated/`; MUST NEVER read `sites/` directly.
- `packages/validators` — Zod schemas and validation only.
- `packages/site-core` — the only **package** allowed to load/read `sites/<siteSlug>/` configuration, content, and assets at runtime / build time.
- `packages/ui` — base UI primitives shared across themes (buttons, containers, grids, etc.).
- `packages/theme-*` — reusable theme packages, one folder per theme. See `20-theme-naming-and-governance.mdc`.
- `packages/seo` — pure functions for SEO, canonical URLs, sitemap, robots, schema.
- `sites/<siteSlug>/` — per-company `site.config.ts`, `content/<locale>/pages/*.json`, and `assets/`.
- `templates/` — site template **sources** copied by `tools/create-site` only (config template, page JSON, assets); MUST NOT embed Node/CLI/runtime logic—only static authored files.
- `tools/site-cli/` — **public CLI dispatcher only**: `pnpm site <create|validate|build|pipeline|build-all|clean> …` routes to internal `tsx` scripts. No business logic here. Per-site commands require `<siteSlug>`; `build-all` and `clean` are repo-wide.
- `tools/create-site/` — scaffolds `sites/<siteSlug>/` by copying `templates/<name>/`, substituting `{{TOKEN}}` placeholders, and renaming `site.config.template.ts` → `site.config.ts` (fs + string replace only). Invoked only via **`pnpm site create <siteSlug>`**. **`pnpm site pipeline <siteSlug>`** runs create → validate → build in one shot (implementation in `scripts/site-pipeline.ts`, not invokable directly).
- `scripts/` — automation scripts invoked only through `pnpm site` (validate, build, pipeline, build-all, clean). `scripts/validate-site.ts` and `scripts/build-site.ts` must access `sites/` ONLY through `packages/site-core`, never via direct filesystem access. Do not run `scripts/*.ts` or `tools/create-site/*.ts` with `pnpm exec tsx` as the supported workflow.
- `functions/` — Cloudflare Pages Functions at the **repo root**, not inside `apps/site-builder/`.

## Build data flow

`sites/<siteSlug>/` → `packages/site-core` reads → `packages/validators` validates → emits JSON into `apps/site-builder/.generated/` → `apps/site-builder` (Astro) renders → `dist/sites/<siteSlug>/`.

Astro must consume only `.generated/`. `sites/` is never imported from inside `apps/`.

## Architecture Freeze (FACTORY v1)

Structural split/refactors are **not** the default roadmap post-v1. Official scope, layering, escape hatch (`SITE_FACTORY_ALLOW_DIRECT_SCRIPTS`), and maintenance-mode criteria are authored in **`docs/factory-v1-final-spec.md`** (FACTORY v1 FINAL SPEC). Treat that document as the versioned freeze record for humans and agents.

**Maintenance governance** (frozen policy: forbid new CLI/pipeline splits/Factory splits; allowed change layers; mandatory v2 triggers; drift risks) lives in **`docs/factory-v1-maintenance-governance.md`**.
